  "source_notes": "Arno Müller, vol 2, states 1 June. However, as pointed out by atr, it is explained on German Wikipedia that his father faked records to enter his son into the military. The minimum age was 12 years; decisive was the age at 1 June in the year of admission.\\n\\nSy Scholfield quotes church record for 1 July in the biography, \"Carl von Clausewitz: Lebensbild eines patriotischen Militars und fortschrittlichen Militärtheoretikers\" by Gerhard Förster (Militärverlag der Deutschen Demokratischen Republik, 1983), p. 1797: \"Danach wurde Carl Philipp Gottlieb, Sohn des Clausewitz, Friedrich Gabriel, am 1. Juli 1780 abends ½ 4 Uhr geboren, getauft am 9. desselben Monats. Da das Kirchenregister ordentlich geführt wurde, ist es durchaus möglich, daß dieses Geburtsdatum stimmt.\" [Translation: Carl Philipp Gottlieb, son of Frederick Gabriel Clausewitz, was born at 3:30pm on July 1, 1780, baptized on the 9th of the same month. Since the church register was properly conducted, it is quite possible that this birth is correct.\"] \\n",
